Step 1: Enable S3 Inventory on Target Buckets
Enable S3 Inventory on each matching bucket (those with "access-logs" or "athena-logs" in the name) via Console, CLI, or CDK/Terraform:

Destination bucket: A central one you control (e.g., your-account-inventory-bucket).

Frequency: Weekly (faster than daily for one-time).

Format: Parquet (efficient for Athena).

Optional fields: Size, LastModifiedDate, StorageClass, ETag.

Filter: Optional prefix if needed.

Wait 24-48 hours for first report (manifest format: bucket/config-id/date/manifest.json). Reports include all objects' metadata.
